# Godot writes its text resources with LF line endings. With core.autocrlf=true
# (the default here) git expects CRLF in the working tree, so every editor save
# shows up as a phantom "modified" diff that vanishes on stage. Pin Godot-authored
# text files to LF so the on-disk form matches what Godot writes — no false diffs,
# and a genuine resource strip is no longer hidden in line-ending noise.
*.tres   text eol=lf
*.tscn   text eol=lf
*.godot  text eol=lf
*.import text eol=lf
*.cfg    text eol=lf
